By way of derogation from Article 5 and without prejudice to Regulation (EC) No 216/2008 and Commission Regulation (EU) No 748/2012

Commission Regulation (EU) No 748/2012 of 3 August 2012 laying down implementing rules for the airworthiness and environmental certification of aircraft and related products, parts and appliances, as well as for the certification of design and production organisations (OJ L 224, 21.8.2012, p. 1).';
                                              related to the permit to fly, flights related to the introduction or modification of aircraft types conducted by design or production organisations within the scope of their privileges, as well as flights carrying no passengers or cargo where the aircraft is ferried for refurbishment, repair, maintenance checks, inspections, delivery, export or similar purposes shall be operated under conditions set out in Member States' national law.
